claim.claim-text:
1. A method for reviewing employee performance, said method comprising: 
receiving planning factor data from a user, the planning factor data corresponding to one or more employees and the planning factor data including reward planning data; 
storing the planning factor data in employee profile data areas, wherein each employee profile data area corresponds to one of the employees; 
evaluating one or more employees, the evaluating resulting in evaluation data; 
storing the evaluation data for each of the evaluated employees in the employee profile data area corresponding to each evaluated employee; and 
analyzing the reward planning data corresponding to one or more employees using the evaluation data corresponding to one or more evaluated employees.

2. The method as described in claim 1 further comprising: 
selecting a group of employees; 
comparing the evaluation data corresponding to one employee in the group of employees to one or more other employees in the group; 
determining whether to revise the evaluation data of the employee; and 
revising evaluation data corresponding to the employee in response to the determining.

3. The method as described in claim 1 further comprising: 
selecting one of the employees; 
identifying the selected employee by a contributor level corresponding to the employee; 
retrieving a planned reward from the reward planning data in response to the determination; 
determining whether to revise the employee profile data corresponding to the employee based on the contribution level and the planned reward; and 
revising the employee profile data in response to the determination.

8. An information handling system comprising: 
one or more processors; 
a memory accessible by the processors; 
one or more nonvolatile storage devices accessible by the processors; and 
an employee performance management tool to evaluate employee performance, the employee performance management tool including: 
means for receiving planning factor data from a user, the planning factor data corresponding to one or more employees and the planning factor data including reward planning data; 
means for storing the planning factor data in employee profile data areas, wherein each employee profile data area corresponds to one of the employees; 
means for evaluating one or more employees, the evaluating resulting in evaluation data; 
means for storing the evaluation data for each of the evaluated employees in the employee profile data area corresponding to each evaluated employee; and 
means for analyzing the reward planning data corresponding to one or more employees using the evaluation data corresponding to one or more evaluated employees.

9. The information handling system as described in claim 8 further comprising: 
means for selecting a group of employees; 
means for comparing the evaluation data corresponding to one employee in the group of employees to one or more other employees in the group; 
means for determining whether to revise the evaluation data of the employee; and 
means for revising evaluation data corresponding to the employee in response to the determining.

10. The information handling system as described in claim 8 further comprising: 
means for selecting one of the employees; 
means for identifying the selected employee by a contributor level corresponding to the employee; 
means for retrieving a planned reward from the reward planning data in response to the determination; 
means for determining whether to revise the employee profile data corresponding to the employee based on the contribution level and the planned reward; and 
means for revising the employee profile data in response to the determination.

14. A computer program product stored in a computer operable media for reviewing employee performance, said computer program product comprising: 
means for receiving planning factor data from a user, the planning factor data corresponding to one or more employees and the planning factor data including reward planning data; 
means for storing the planning factor data in employee profile data areas, wherein each employee profile data area corresponds to one of the employees; 
means for evaluating one or more employees, the evaluating resulting in evaluation data; 
means for storing the evaluation data for each of the evaluated employees in the employee profile data area corresponding to each evaluated employee; and 
means for analyzing the reward planning data corresponding to one or more employees using the evaluation data corresponding to one or more evaluated employees.

15. The computer program product as described in claim 14 further comprising: 
means for selecting a group of employees; 
means for comparing the evaluation data corresponding to one employee in the group of employees to one or more other employees in the group; 
means for determining whether to revise the evaluation data of the employee; and 
means for revising evaluation data corresponding to the employee in response to the determining.

16. The computer program product as described in claim 14 further comprising: 
means for selecting one of the employees; 
means for identifying the selected employee by a contributor level corresponding to the employee; 
means for retrieving a planned reward from the reward planning data in response to the determination; 
means for determining whether to revise the employee profile data corresponding to the employee based on the contribution level and the planned reward; and 
means for revising the employee profile data in response to the determination.
